<AbstractNarration>Filaseta&lt;br/&gt;0207302&lt;br/&gt;     The investigator and his collaborator Douglas Meade develop&lt;br/&gt;and implement efficient algorithms for irreducibility testing and&lt;br/&gt;factorization of polynomials with small Euclidean norm.  In&lt;br/&gt;addition, they classify through similar algorithms all cases&lt;br/&gt;where reducibility occurs with Euclidean norm bounded by some&lt;br/&gt;prescribed amount.  Issues relating to the complexity and&lt;br/&gt;parallel implementation of such algorithms are considered.&lt;br/&gt;     Both factoring and, more generally, computational&lt;br/&gt;mathematics have played a vital role in cryptography.  The&lt;br/&gt;importance of algorithms in such applications continues to&lt;br/&gt;increase as technology advances.  This project deals with&lt;br/&gt;factoring polynomials of high degree from both a theoretical and&lt;br/&gt;computational point of view.  The work has application in&lt;br/&gt;cryptography and in complexity theory, which deals with the&lt;br/&gt;question of how much work is needed to solve certain kinds of&lt;br/&gt;problems.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
